               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism and philosophy, 38 items (a-ll)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111616 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100934">
                  <summary>Substantive collection of miscellaneous Persian and Arabic works on Shīʿī tradition, ethics, Sufism, metaphysics, and philosophy compiled from various named and anonymous sources. All items are the work of the same scribal hand on a consistent type of thin, high-quality paper. The volume is not dated, but may be datable to the early to mid-seventeenth century on the basis of internal references in items n and hh. The Shīʿī emphasis of many works may suggest origins in Iran or particular centres of sectarian learning in the Indian provinces, such as the Deccan and elsewhere. Neat and disciplined Persian scribal naskh throughout; catchwords occasionally in shikastah. Limited annotations in margins. Stamped and faint Persian foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged (patches of combed marble paper and ornamental printed paper pasted over pasteboard with brown leather edging and spine), labelled; torn and pasted over; pasteboards cracked. Folios mostly unbound, cropped, stained, extensive wormholes, later repairs. Condition extremely fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="17r">ff. 1v-17r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Fragment from an excerpt of a rare edition of the metaphysical treatise on the relationship of man and other spiritual beings evidently by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656473.0x000001 viaf_211269318" role="aut">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName> (d. 707/1307-8), although his name does not appear in the work. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is defective at the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is divided into four bāb. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22246">Jāvidān'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22246">جاودان نامه</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="Supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656473.0x000001 viaf_211269318">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="Supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656473.0x000001 viaf_211269318">افضل الدّين محمّد كاشى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
