                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item4">
                     <locus from="29v" to="59v">ff. 29v-59v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Philosophical treatise on the nature of the ego based largely on Arabic versions of the work on the same subject by Arisṭāṭālīs or <persName key="viaf_7524651" role="ant">Aristotle</persName>, the <title>De Anima</title>, evidently by <persName key="viaf_211269318" role="aut">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName> (d. 707/1307-8), according to <persName key="viaf_10017206" role="cataloguer">Rieu</persName>, <persName key="viaf_64248843" role="cataloguer">Ethé</persName>, and <persName key="viaf_73981096" role="cataloguer">Levy</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The introduction is followed by three discourses termed maqālah. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22247">Kitāb-i nafs</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22247">كتاب نفس</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_211269318">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item5">
                     <locus from="59v" to="82r">ff. 59v-82r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Metaphysical treatise on knowledge on the nature of being and substance, evidently by <persName key="viaf_211269318" role="aut">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName> (d. 707/1307-8). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Written at the request of religious fraternities in the city of Rayy. 
</p>
                        <p>The work consists of eight sections termed dar-i sukhan in accordance with the title. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22248">Dar-i sukhan</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22248">در سخن</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_211269318">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_211269318">افضل الدّين محمّد كاشى</persName>
