                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item6">
                     <locus from="82r" to="82v">ff. 82r-82v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. </p>
                        <p>Untitled metaphysical treatise on thought and the power of the mind evidently by <persName key="viaf_211269318" role="aut">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName> (d. 707/1307-8), whose name appears in red ink at the beginning as <persName key="viaf_211269318" role="aut">Bābā Afz̤al Kāshī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is followed by a short note on the soul and corporeality by an unnamed author, evidently by the same <persName key="viaf_211269318" role="aut">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
