                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. </p>
                        <p>Sufi treatise in a homiletic tone on essential and incidental aspects of life, though labelled <title>ʿArz̤'nāmah</title> above, the work refers to itself as <title>nāmah-'i humāyūn</title>. Although the author is not mentioned, the work is evidently attributable to <persName key="viaf_211269318" role="att">Afz̤al al-Dīn Muḥammad Kāshī</persName> (d. 707/1307-8), and supported by <persName key="viaf_10017206" role="cataloguer">Rieu</persName>, <persName key="viaf_64248843" role="cataloguer">Ethé</persName>, and <persName key="viaf_73981096" role="cataloguer">Levy</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22249">ʿArz̤'nāmah</title>
