                        <p>Item ee. </p>
                        <p>Arabic commentary on the celebrated Sufi treatise <title>Fuṣūṣ al-ḥikam</title> of <persName key="viaf_95223177" role="ant">Ibn al-ʿArabī</persName> (d. 638/1240) by his disciple, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656932.0x000001 viaf_261622843" role="aut">Muḥammad Ṣadr al-Dīn ibn Isḥāq al-Qūnavī</persName> (d. 673/1274). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2401">Maṭlaʿ khuṣūṣ al-kilam fī maʿānī Fuṣūṣ al-ḥikam</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_2401">مطلع خصوص الكلم فى معانى فصوص الحكم</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656932.0x000001 viaf_261622843">Muḥammad Ṣadr al-Dīn ibn Isḥāq al-Qūnavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656932.0x000001 viaf_261622843">محمّد صدر الدّين ابن اسحٰق القونوى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="32" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item32">
                     <locus from="228r" to="228v">ff. 228r-228v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item ff. </p>
                        <p>Excerpt from an untitled treatise metaphysical perception by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="33" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item33">
                     <locus from="228v" to="229r">ff. 228v-229r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item gg. </p>
                        <p>Excerpts from the Arabic collection of Shīʿī aḥādīs̲, the <title>Kitāb al-tawḥīd</title> of <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658841.0x000001 viaf_90043815" role="aut">Shaykh Ṣadūq</persName>, that is, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658841.0x000001 viaf_90043815" role="aut">Abū Jaʿfar Muḥammad al-Bābavayh al-Qummī</persName> (d. 381/991). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22250">Kitāb al-tawḥīd</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22250">كتاب التّوحيد</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658841.0x000001 viaf_90043815">Shaykh Ṣadūq</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658841.0x000001 viaf_90043815">شيخ صدوق</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="34" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item34">
                     <locus from="229r" to="270r">ff. 229r-270r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item hh. </p>
                        <p>Treatise by an unnamed editor abridging the larger treatise collecting mystical, ethical and religious comments and dicta in Arabic and Persian without any apparent order, the <title>al-Kalimāt al-maknūnah</title> by <persName key="person_f7366" role="ant">Muḥammad ibn Murtaz̤á</persName>, known as <persName key="person_f7366" role="ant">Muḥsin Kāshī</persName> (d. circa 1090/1679). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22251">al-Laʾālī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22251">اللّآلى</title>
                     <author/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="35" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item35">
                     <locus from="270r" to="277r">ff. 270r-277r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item ii. </p>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled Persian translation by an unnamed translator of the philosophical and semi-mystical legend of <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657024.0x000001 viaf_303455886" role="subject">Ḥayy ibn Yaqẓān</persName> (here written nuqṣān) related in Arabic by <persName key="viaf_89770781" role="ant">Avicenna</persName>, that is <persName key="viaf_89770781" role="ant">Abū ʿAlī Ḥusayn ibn ʿAbd Allāh ibn Sīnā al-Bukhārī</persName> (d. 428/1037). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was commissioned by the <orgName>Kakawayhid</orgName> ruler of <placeName>Isfahan</placeName>, <persName key="person_f7081" role="pat">ʿAz̤ud al-Dīn ʿAlāʾ al-Dawlah Fakhr al-Millah Tāj al-Ummah Abū Jaʿfar Ḥusām [Muḥammad] ibn Dushmanyār</persName>, entitled here <persName key="person_f7081" role="pat">Amīr al-Muʾminīn</persName> (d. 433/1041-2). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Portions of the Arabic original are given along with the Persian translation.  
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="36" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_805-item36">
